<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880208-0151 </DOCNO><HL> Bank of Dallas Closes; Deposits Are Switched To a New State Bank </HL><SO> </SO><CO> GOVMT </CO><IN> BNK TNM </IN><DATELINE> WASHINGTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Regulators closed Bank of Dallas and transferred its deposits to Deposit Guaranty Bank, a newly chartered state bank, according to the Federal Deposit Insurance Corp. Both banks are based in Dallas.    Bank of Dallas's two offices were scheduled to reopen today as branches of Deposit Guaranty.    Aside from taking over $170.2 million in deposits from Bank of Dallas, the new bank bought $162.6 million of the failed bank's assets at a discount of $65 million. The closure brought the number of bank failures nationwide this year to 18; seven were in Texas. </TEXT></DOC>